Sentencas: A parametric analysis is carried out to study the effects of the operating conditions on the performance and operation of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: The computational fluid dynamics model incorporates mass, momentum, species and energy balances along with ionic and electronic charge transfers.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: Effects of temperature, fuel flow rate, fuel composition, anode pressure and cathode pressure on fuel cell performance are investigated.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: Polarization curves are compared to allow an understanding of the effects of different operating conditions on the performance of the fuel cell.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: Effects of anode flow rate on fuel cell efficiency and fuel utilization are also investigated.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: Moreover, influence of operating temperature on the internal electronic current leaks is outlined.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: Temperature distributions, current density profiles and hydrogen mole fraction profiles are also utilized to have a better understanding of the spatial effects of operating parameters.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: It is predicted that at 550 degrees C, for an output current demand of 0.53 A cm(-2), fuel cell needs to generate 0.65 A cm(-2) ionic current density where the difference in these values is attributed to internal current leaks.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)

Sentencas: On the other hand for temperatures lower than 500 degrees C, the effect of electronic leakage currents are not significant.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)
